          </p>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code="curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OpenCompanyApp/kosmokrator/main/install.sh | bash" lang="bash" />
          </div>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code={integration.setup.mcp_gateway_install_command} lang="bash" />
          </div>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code={mcpJson} lang="json" />
          </div>

          <h2>Serve Manually</h2>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code={integration.setup.mcp_gateway_serve_command} lang="bash" />
          </div>

          <h2>MCP Tool Names</h2>
          <p>KosmoKrator exposes integration tools through the gateway with stable names:</p>
          {integration.tools.length > 10 ? (
            <details class="raw-docs-details" open>
              <summary>MCP Tool Names ({integration.tools.length} tools)</summary>
              <div class="tool-table-wrapper">
                <table>
                  <thead><tr><th>MCP tool</th><th>Source function</th><th>Type</th></tr></thead>
                  <tbody>
                    {integration.tools.map((tool) => (
                      <tr>
                        <td data-label="MCP tool"><code class="text-kosmo-rose">{toolMcpName(integration, tool)}</code></td>
                        <td data-label="Source"><code class="text-kosmo-rose">{toolFullName(integration, tool)}</code></td>
                        <td data-label="Type">{operationLabel(tool.type)} <code class="text-kosmo-rose">{tool.type}</code></td>
                      </tr>
                    ))}
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </details>
          ) : (
            <div class="tool-table-wrapper">
              <table>
                <thead><tr><th>MCP tool</th><th>Source function</th><th>Type</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody>
                  {integration.tools.map((tool) => (
                    <tr>
                      <td data-label="MCP tool"><code class="text-kosmo-rose">{toolMcpName(integration, tool)}</code></td>
                      <td data-label="Source"><code class="text-kosmo-rose">{toolFullName(integration, tool)}</code></td>
                      <td data-label="Type">{operationLabel(tool.type)} <code class="text-kosmo-rose">{tool.type}</code></td>
                    </tr>
                  ))}
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          )}

          <h2>Write Access</h2>
          <p>
            Start with <code class="text-kosmo-rose">--write=deny</code> for read-only MCP clients. Use <code class="text-kosmo-rose">--write=ask</code> or
            <code class="text-kosmo-rose"> --write=allow</code> only when the client and workspace are trusted.
          </p>
        </section>
      )}

      {pageType === 'framework' && client && (
        <section class="integration-copy min-w-0 grid gap-4 max-w-[1080px]">
          <h2>Connect {integration.name} to {client.label}</h2>
          <p>{client.description}</p>
          <p>
            {client.configIntro} The gateway is local, scoped to this integration, and starts with
            <code class="text-kosmo-rose"> --write=deny</code> so {client.shortLabel} can inspect read-capable tools without receiving write access by default.
          </p>

          <h2>{integration.name} MCP Config for {client.label}</h2>
          <p>{client.installHint}</p>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code={clientMcpJson} lang="json" />
          </div>

          <h2>Run the Gateway Manually</h2>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code={integration.setup.mcp_gateway_serve_command} lang="bash" />
          </div>

          <h2>Why Use KosmoKrator Here</h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr))] gap-3">
            <div class="p-4 border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg bg-white/[0.04]"><strong>Scoped tools</strong><p>Expose only {integration.name} instead of a broad multi-service tool list.</p></div>
            <div class="p-4 border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg bg-white/[0.04]"><strong>Local credentials</strong><p>Reuse credentials already configured for the KosmoKrator CLI and Lua runtime.</p></div>
            <div class="p-4 border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg bg-white/[0.04]"><strong>Write policy</strong><p>Start read-only, then opt into ask or allow for trusted workspaces.</p></div>
          </div>

          <h2>{integration.name} Tools Visible to {client.shortLabel}</h2>
          <p>{client.shortLabel} sees stable MCP tool names generated from the {integration.name} integration catalog.</p>
          <div class="tool-table-wrapper">
            <table>
              <thead><tr><th>MCP tool</th><th>Source function</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                {integration.tools.slice(0, 30).map((tool) => (
                  <tr>
                    <td data-label="MCP tool"><code class="text-kosmo-rose">{toolMcpName(integration, tool)}</code></td>
                    <td data-label="Source"><code class="text-kosmo-rose">{toolFullName(integration, tool)}</code></td>
                    <td data-label="Type">{operationLabel(tool.type)}</td>
                    <td data-label="Description">{tool.description || tool.short_description || tool.name}</td>
                  </tr>
                ))}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          {integration.tools.length > 30 && <p>Showing 30 of {integration.tools.length} functions. See the <a href={integrationUrl(integration, 'mcp')}>{integration.name} MCP reference</a> for the full list.</p>}

          <h2>Related {integration.name} Pages</h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr))] gap-3">
            <a class="grid gap-1.5 p-4 border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg bg-white/[0.04] text-kosmo-text no-underline" href={integrationUrl(integration, 'cli')}><strong>{integration.name} CLI</strong><span>Use direct JSON commands instead of MCP discovery.</span></a>
            <a class="grid gap-1.5 p-4 border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg bg-white/[0.04] text-kosmo-text no-underline" href={integrationUrl(integration, 'mcp')}><strong>{integration.name} MCP</strong><span>Full gateway reference and MCP tool names.</span></a>
            <a class="grid gap-1.5 p-4 border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg bg-white/[0.04] text-kosmo-text no-underline" href={`/mcp/${client.slug}`}><strong>KosmoKrator for {client.shortLabel}</strong><span>Client-level gateway setup.</span></a>
          </div>
        </section>
      )}

      {pageType === 'environment' && environment && (
        <section class="integration-copy min-w-0 grid gap-4 max-w-[1080px]">
          <h2>{integration.name} CLI for {environment.titleSuffix}</h2>
          <p>{environment.description}</p>
          <p>
            {environment.exampleIntro} The {integration.name} CLI uses the same integration registry as the TUI, Lua runtime, and MCP gateway,
            but returns predictable command output for automation.
          </p>

          <h2>Command Shape</h2>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code={environmentSnippet} lang="bash" />
          </div>

          <h2>Discovery Before Execution</h2>
          <p>Agents and scripts can inspect {integration.name} docs and schemas before choosing a function.</p>
          <div class="code-frame my-0.5 mb-4 p-4 overflow-auto border border-kosmo-white-border-strong rounded-lg leading-relaxed bg-kosmo-code-bg">
            <Code code={discoverySnippet} lang="bash" />
          </div>

          <h2>Useful {integration.name} CLI Functions</h2>
          <div class="tool-table-wrapper">
            <table>
              <thead><tr><th>Function</th><th>Type</th><th>Parameters</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                {integration.tools.slice(0, 40).map((tool) => (
                  <tr>
                    <td data-label="Function"><code class="text-kosmo-rose">{toolFullName(integration, tool)}</code></td>
                    <td data-label="Type">{operationLabel(tool.type)}</td>
                    <td data-label="Parameters">{parameterSummary(tool)}</td>
                    <td data-label="Description">{tool.description || tool.short_description || tool.name}</td>
                  </tr>
                ))}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          {integration.tools.length > 40 && <p>Showing 40 of {integration.tools.length} functions. See the <a href={integrationUrl(integration, 'cli')}>{integration.name} CLI reference</a> for every function.</p>}

          <h2>Automation Notes</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Use <code class="text-kosmo-rose">--json</code> for machine-readable output.</li>
            <li>Keep credentials out of argv by using environment variables or stored KosmoKrator configuration.</li>
            <li>Configure read/write policy before unattended runs; use <code class="text-kosmo-rose">--force</code> only for trusted automation.</li>
            <li>Use the MCP gateway instead when the agent needs dynamic tool discovery inside a conversation.</li>
